 <html:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f\colon  A\to  B]]></fr:tex> be <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-001T.xml" title="n-truncated map" addr="forest://erct/erct-001T" type="local">contractible</fr:link>; we define a section <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[s\colon  B\to  A]]></fr:tex> to take <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[b:B]]></fr:tex> to the first component of the centre of contraction of the <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-001Q.xml" title="fiber" addr="forest://erct/erct-001Q" type="local">fiber</fr:link> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f]]></fr:tex> over <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[b]]></fr:tex>. The witness <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[h_s\colon  f\circ  s\sim  1_{B}]]></fr:tex> exhibiting <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[s]]></fr:tex> as a section of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f]]></fr:tex>, we use the second component of the centre of contraction.</html:p>
